\par For the Week Ending March 27, 1943
\par 
\par 
\par 1. The accompanying tabulation of morale indications is not subdivid\-ed this week according to source as has been done in previous reports. The great increase, in mail routed through this office and the sharp reduct
ion in examining staff made it impossible to spot check much unit censored mail, aside from postcards which provide no good indications of morale. It was also necessary to spot check officers' mail from many scattered units and localities, so that a subdi
vided tabulation would not provide enough letters in any single category to give reliable percentages. The combined tabulat\-
ion that is presented is based mainly on officers' mail but is otherwise a fair sampling of all the units represented in mail flowing through this office.
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3702390 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13261201\charrsid13261201 GENERAL MORALE }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13261201 
